<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uyarnorbs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>YarNorbs</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/00 9:48:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> Rules,,<br>
If your pulling in Trak, LOSE the wis and get<br>
your MR gear on..<br>
<br>
Lose the Thorn buff. any damage done to a Summoning<br>
mob will cause them to summon you. You will die!!<br>
<br>
Pull only with snare. Or aggro. Pull Doom with snare<br>
since he runs almost at sow speed snared. He summons.<br>
But wont summon unless hes Hurt.GET THAT IN YOUR HEAD!!<br>
<br>
Never ever damage a mob during the pull if you wish<br>
to be alive long enough to get to the pull<br>
to your group.<br>
<br>
The MR will save your hide during the pull. At least<br>
get it to 95+<br>
<br>
Root the mobs you pick up on the pull with ensnaring<br>
roots. Since it's a 1.8 cast time Its great.<br>
<br>
When you have aggroed many mobs. If you have it.<br>
Cast egress to eliminate any aggro you have left<br>
behind you.<br>
<br>
Always have Cheatah up and ready. Chances are your<br>
gate will not get off if your in big trouble.<br>
Heh Trak is full of shaman rooters. MR MR MR....<br>
<br>
These are the basics. Rules are strict on Hurt pulling.<br>
<br>
YarNorbs FootStomper -55- <br>
Erollisi Marr.<br>
Divine Grace. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/ukoshyoftribunal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Koshy of Tribunal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/1/00 11:27:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> &quot;Lose the Thorn buff. any damage done to a Summoning<br>
mob will cause them to summon you. You will die!!<br>
<br>
Pull only with snare. Or aggro. Pull Doom with snare<br>
since he runs almost at sow speed snared. He summons.<br>
But wont summon unless hes Hurt.GET THAT IN YOUR HEAD!!&quot;<br>
<br>
No, you have to do at least 10% of their total hit point of damage before they start summoning.  If a 5 to 6hp thorn (or in my case, bladecoat) is gonna do 10% of their total hit point of damage, you'll be dead long before you get summoned (especially since against doom you'll most likely be exchanging 6hps for 150+hps smacks).<br>
<br>
There aren't too many &quot;rare&quot; named mobs in Trak that's over level 51 so the odds of you getting summoned is pretty low.  But definately keep your MR up since those stupid froggie shamans do root A LOT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dr00dlfg>dr00dLFG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/27/01 9:40:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utulasbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TulasBrell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 11:19:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> The hunter cycle appears to be slightly higher level than the forager cycle. In doing the forager cycle countless times I have never once been summoned, and often pull with fury of air.  So the whole ruleset about MR just posted above I would say is not really necessary for Trak pulling if you are just doing the forager cycle.<br>
<br>
I also would not recommend casting egress to remove agro. Egress costs a huge amount of mana, has a long casting time and takes you to another part of the zone. Much simpler to just camp out now and then between pulls to wipe the agro list.  <br>
<br>
Camping is better to remove agro than egress, and gate is better to escape than egress. Egress was simply only good as a nice little in-zone travel spell to get some where faster till verant ruined it by making the zone reload to remove agro.<br>
<br>
Spirit of Cheetah is also something I wouldn't recommend as it is short duration and takes a valuable spell slot.  Plus it overrides sow, so that when it fades you no longer have any speed boost. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umulerin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mulerin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/30/01 6:53:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> &quot;Pull only with snare. Or aggro. Pull Doom with snare since he runs almost at sow speed snared. He summons.  But wont summon unless hes Hurt.GET THAT IN YOUR HEAD!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Dispell is a great way to pull casters.  Another thing to do is to root the pet of the mob if they have one.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lose the Thorn buff. any damage done to a Summoning mob will cause them to summon you. You will die!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Keep the thorncoat line up.  Any mob that can summon you from whacking your coat will die from you meleeing it because it'll have no hps.  Dmg shield is another story.<br>
<br>
&quot;Root the mobs you pick up on the pull with ensnaring roots. Since it's a 1.8 cast time Its great.&quot;<br>
<br>
Actually, I'd prefer ensnare.  Same cast time, less likely to be resisted, and typically you're pulling from a long distance so you'll lose the mob during the run.  Finally, then you have 10 mins of constant pulling while that mob is pissed at you instead of the duration of root (max 3 mins).<br>
<br>
&quot;When you have aggroed many mobs. If you have it. Cast egress to eliminate any aggro you have left behind you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Or obviously zone/camp out.  Why blow the mana when you can outrun any mob in Trak's teeth that isn't on the cycle and just zone?<br>
<br>
&quot;But wont summon unless hes Hurt.GET THAT IN YOUR HEAD!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Any druid doing this cycle that doesn't know that is 1) Ebay 2) Too low a lvl to be doing the cycle anyway.<br>
<br>
Final thing: Use the terrain to your advantage.  I always keep lev up because hills and lakes slow mobs down, while I'm running away from them.<br>
<br>
Mulerin Wulfkin<br>
60th on Karana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unaluvien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naluvien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/1/01 4:31:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> Sorry, you do not have to do ANY damage to a mob to get summoned, much less 10%.<br>
<br>
Here's how it works.  A mob will not summon unless it has been damaged (ANY amount will do), and then it will summon whoever is highest on its agro list.  I've personally ran away from and zoned on guardian wurms quite a few times when I stepped too close.  They never summon me unless I damage them (which I will never do unless I'm looking to die fast).  If you doubt this, here is a simple way that will prove it.  Get your guild and go down to the Juggs.  As soon as the tanks agro the Jug, cast Fixation of Ro on it.  They really like it when Druids use this spell on them.  I promise, you will get an immediate invitation to join Mr. Jugg, and you will notice that YOU'VE done NO damage.  I assume you've already noticed this?  So where are you coming up with this 10% figure?<br>
<br>
Obviously, you've never pulled TT.  You have thorncoat, he hits you, he gets damaged, he summons, you die.  You don't believe?  Go try it! :)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/1/01 6:19:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> 5 to 10 percent damage must be done to the mob.  Yes this has been proven.  Thorn coat is not likely to cause this damage.  No one said you had to do the damage.  It just has to occur is all, it doesn't matter how it happens.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah dispell is the ultimate pulling tool.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cron</A> at: 5/1/01 6:21:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umulerin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mulerin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/1/01 6:30:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> Naluvien - You're correct in your example but the conclusion you draw is incorrect...<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, when I said cast I non-damage spell so you didn't get summoned I assumed everyone know what I was saying.  The correct phrasing is you should use a spell that isn't considered as massive damage to the mob to pull it.  The 5 to 10% figure IS correct after all.  That is why you can root mobs once or twice w/out being summoned (you still do 150+ dmg) but after repeated roots you will be summoned.  That is also why when you heal (counted at dmg done to a mob on aggro list), cast Ro's Fiery (debuff counted as dmg to aggro list), etc you get summoned.  The amount of aggro is larger than that 5%-10%...so story is to pull w/dispell, ensnare, flamelick, or any other lvl 1 dd which is guarenteed to be below the summoning threshhold.<br>
<br>
I personally like dispell because ensnare has a larger value and will get you aggro'd faster if you heal during the fight.  Also, I hate (in most cases) having to run a snared mob long distances, as is the case in Trak's Teeth and finally, dispell will get rid of those annoying Frog Shaman buffs that the hunter/forager get while wandering. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utippen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tippen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/2/01 6:33:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> Why cast anything to pull the rares?  Just aggro-pull them.  Run up near them, they aggro and back to camp you go.<br>
<br>
/shrug <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utulasbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TulasBrell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/3/01 2:25:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> Tippen -- <br>
<br>
Because sometimes the forager or rare is near another MOB and you don't want to agro the other one. And because sometimes the forager or rare is zig zagging and hard to catch and stopping to cast a spell pulls him more efficiently. When possible, just running into it to agro it is the best way, but it's not always possible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utippen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tippen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/3/01 6:01:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> One of the cool things with Trak's Teeth is that mobs lose interest REAL quick if you get far from them.  If I pick up a sow'd shaman that I'd rather not take back to camp, I'll stop and snare him then continue on.<br>
<br>
I pull there a lot and the only mob I bother to pull with a spell is Doom (hehe... tried aggro pulling him once, result was dead halfling... he's fast!).<br>
<br>
That said, we usually do the forager cycle, so I'm not as familiar with all the hunter cycle rares.<br>
<br>
Anyway, just hadn't seen any one mention aggro pulling in Trak and thought I'd throw that in.  Whatever works for you is fine :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualicardlonewolfii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alicard Lonewolf II</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/3/01 7:16:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> *cough* Solo'd doom *cough*<br>
