<BR>Preserver of the Glade, <a href="http://www.aradani.com/warcouncil">The War Council</a>, Saryrn
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utulasbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TulasBrell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/3/01 4:18:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> No I'm not joking, Aldarion, it's usually a waste of a spell slot.  It is one of those spells which look great on paper but in practice doesn't cut it.  10-15 minute load time sure doesn't help, and it doesn't last that long either. Only 8 spell slots to go around and mine are full with spells I must have memmed.<br>
<br>
Also, please keep in mind that in trak's teeth a good puller must weave around MOBs constantly, and that is much harder if you are going too fast.  If one does use SoC anyway, I sure hope people don't run back to their group, as the number one rule of pulling is don't train your group.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ublackwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blackwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/5/01 9:57:19 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Blackwulf?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone seen Hierophant Ixyl in Trak's Teeth?</span><hr size=1> SoC as a defining spell....okay,whatever.  I've memmed it a handful of times in 56 levels, used it less.  Only place I habitually mem it is pulling in Fear.  The long recast/refresh time, the overwrite of SoW/wolfform, its never proven worthwhile to me.  Snare and SoW do just fine 99.9% of the time for me.<br>
<br>
*<br>
<br>
Summoning mobs.  Follow with me the rules of summoning mobs:<br>
<br>
1)51st level +<br>
2) you are on the agro list (your actions, simple passed agro, whatever)<br>
3) the mob takes 10% + damage from _any source.<br>
<br>
If these three conditions are met, the mob will start summoning.  I work the 'named' cycle in SF a lot, and many of the mobs I pull are potentially 51st+.  IF I root/drones of doom then, then drop a lightnig strike off the lum stick, that's when I find out the hard way if they summon.<br>
<br>
Simple passed agro is enough to get you killed in Skyfire.  Pair of mages I know were working the BW zone, had a wurm (simple wurm, never summons) run and get away.  o~o  Short while later, one of the mages gets summoned out in the middle of the zone and killed by a mob he had never seen.<br>
<br>
*<br>
<br>
MR is nice in TT, the shaman are annoying.  When I'm feeling a touch paranoid, I buff RM.  But, normally I just have lev, wolf, bladecoat and invis when I pull.  Sometimes SLN, and/or regen, if I got beat on.  Works just fine, thanks to the level difference.  When I was a 51st druid soloing for his seb key, then I was buffing RM all the time, and needed it. <p>Blackwulf, 55th druid <BR>
Bristlebane <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubroomhilda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Broomhilda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/7/01 8:43:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> I have to butt in here and agree and disagree with some of you that SoC IS almost a must-have-mem'd spell depending on what your doing.  If none of you are ever using this spell then your missing out on a spell that'll save your life better than any other spell we have.  You guys ever run into anything that moves at SOW speed(Avengers/Elites/Chief buffed by oracle in EW, Doom in TT, Death Squads, Othmirs, etc)?  If so how did you get away?  Maybe you got that lucky Gate off when they were double hitting you for 150, or you luckily zoned as they were on your ass SoW'd hitting you as you ran.  In most cases your dead, since your only option is to Gate or zone.  Good luck getting that gate off or finding that zone everytime before they pound you to death.  I ALWAYS keep SoC mem'd when i'm outdoors, and i cant tell you how many times its saved my ass.  From SoW'd avengers to SoW'd Othmirs when i've had 1 bub of life left, i've made it out alive because of SoC, nothing else we have would've saved me since there is no way i'm gonna get a gate off when i have multiple mobs double hitting me for 100's.  Heh, i'm not gonna even debate this if anybody disagrees with the usefulness of SoC but all i can tell you is your missing out big time if you dont ever keep it mem'd.  <br>
<br>
The thing is even though it only lasts a short duration, in that time you can almost always get far enough away to lose aggro as long as your running straight in that direction.  We've all had SOW run out at the worst times right?  Just SoC then recast SOW once SoC fades.  The ONLY times i dont have it mem'd are when i'm indoors(interchange with Gate) or grouped(altho sometimes still keep mem'd but usually not because i usually stay and die with group).  I look at SoC as one of our most valuable and most underrated spells, to me the equivalent of a life saver as feign Death.  I cant emphasize enough the usefulness of this spell =).<br>
<br>
In terms of summoning mobs, i had experience with Yvolcarn in CS who summons.  He's now hit me 2 separate times when i've had Thorncoat up and i never got summoned.  Heh, maybe my SoC right after i see 'Yvolcarn hits you for 100' prevented the summoning, who knows?, but i've yet to be summoned from a summoning mob hitting my thorncoat.  Although i dont get hit too often by summoning mobs if i can help it.  <br>
<br>
